142
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:14,960
Gi Chan.

143
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:19,900
I'll put this to good use.
Thank you.

144
00:09:25,570 --> 00:09:28,210
First, I have to get out
of this filthy dump.

145
00:09:37,110 --> 00:09:38,180
Hello,
is this the insurance company?

146
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,320
Well...

147
00:09:41,590 --> 00:09:45,220
I'm calling to claim
a life insurance benefit.

148
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:47,860
I was wondering
what documents I'll need.

149
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:51,700
The insurance is for Hwang Gi Chan.

150
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:54,170
His date of birth...

151
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:57,640
is 880824.

152
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:02,610
My name is Noh Sook Ja.

153
00:10:05,110 --> 00:10:06,310
Excuse me?

154
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:08,810
What do you mean by that?

155
00:10:09,950 --> 00:10:13,920
Wait.
If I'm not the beneficiary, who is?

156
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:21,490
Yes, Teo.
I'm so glad Ji Ho's adjusting well.

157
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:24,900
It's all thanks to you, Jae In.
Thanks for calling so often...

158
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:26,360
and being so thoughtful.

159
00:10:27,030 --> 00:10:29,870
- How have you been?
- Great, thanks to you.

160
00:10:30,470 --> 00:10:33,470
The gallery you designed
just finished construction,

161
00:10:33,470 --> 00:10:35,070
and an exhibition is opening soon.

162
00:10:35,540 --> 00:10:37,510
I'd like to invite you.
Do you want to come visit the gallery?

163
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:41,250
I'd love to.
Let me know when the date is set.

164
00:10:41,950 --> 00:10:43,410
Okay. Talk to you later.

165
00:10:47,990 --> 00:10:50,390
You wench!
Give me the money for my son's life!

166
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:53,390
Who are you to steal my son's money?

167
00:10:53,390 --> 00:10:54,990
Get away from me!

168
00:10:56,990 --> 00:10:58,200
What do you think you're doing?

169
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:01,500
Stay out of this! She's a thief!

170
00:11:01,630 --> 00:11:04,740
She pocketed the money
from my son's death.

171
00:11:04,740 --> 00:11:09,240
How can you say that
when you stole my father's life?

172
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:11,080
You think she's a monster?

173
00:11:11,380 --> 00:11:13,010
- Your son,
- What...

174
00:11:13,010 --> 00:11:16,310
Hwang Gi Chan, transferred
the rights. What's it to you?

175
00:11:16,350 --> 00:11:17,650
Apologize to her right now.

176
00:11:17,650 --> 00:11:21,520
That's crazy! Why would my son
give the rights to her?

177
00:11:21,550 --> 00:11:25,060
It's the price of his life.
When his own mother is still here?

178
00:11:25,090 --> 00:11:26,590
He gave it to her?

179
00:11:27,730 --> 00:11:29,760
You've got to be kidding me!

180
00:11:30,730 --> 00:11:33,730
This is Gi Chan's will.
It was even notarized.

181
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:37,030
His stocks, property,
and his life insurance payout...

182
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:40,740
are to be entrusted to me.
Here, see for yourself.

183
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:50,150
You think I'm going to believe
this scrap of paper?

184
00:11:50,610 --> 00:11:52,850
You think I can't tell it's a fake?

185
00:11:55,590 --> 00:11:56,590
Give me my money!

186
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:59,160
Give me the price of my son's life!

187
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:09,030
Darn.

188
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:10,870
Mom, what's wrong?

189
00:12:19,010 --> 00:12:20,210
That crazy jerk!

190
00:12:20,610 --> 00:12:22,910
How could he be so blinded
by a girl...

191
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:25,950
that he'd mistreat his own mother,
even in death?

192
00:12:26,950 --> 00:12:29,250
You're the most ungrateful son
who ever lived!

193
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:32,890
Rot in the fiery pit!

194
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:36,490
After everything I did for him!

195
00:12:37,260 --> 00:12:40,060
I gave him the world!

196
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:43,900
Of all people,

197
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:47,570
how could he give it to Kang Jae In?

198
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:51,740
When his own mother
is standing right here?

199
00:12:53,110 --> 00:12:55,310
You're no son of mine!

200
00:12:56,110 --> 00:12:58,850
You're not my son!

201
00:13:09,460 --> 00:13:13,860
Did Gi Chan really
leave the insurance money to you?

202
00:13:14,930 --> 00:13:16,000
Yes, he did.

203
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:20,670
My mom's furious about it.
She's completely losing her mind.

204
00:13:21,640 --> 00:13:23,970
She won't stop cursing him out.
It's a total nightmare.

205
00:13:27,510 --> 00:13:29,710
So, listen.

206
00:13:30,950 --> 00:13:32,080
That money...

207
00:13:33,420 --> 00:13:35,390
Can't you give it to my mom?

208
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:39,420
I can't do that.

209
00:13:40,420 --> 00:13:43,330
I'm begging you.
My mom has completely lost her mind.

210
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:47,500
I was so scared she was going
to take it out on me again,

211
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:49,230
so I just panicked and ran away.

212
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:53,840
The money from your brother
wasn't for me.

213
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:57,610
He wanted me to use it
for you and Gi Man.

214
00:13:57,980 --> 00:13:59,710
That's why he appointed me
as your legal guardian.

215
00:14:01,310 --> 00:14:02,450
Why?

216
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:05,220
So your mother
couldn't get the insurance money,

217
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:08,050
and to protect you and Gi Man.

218
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:10,920
That was his final wish.

219
00:14:14,790 --> 00:14:16,130
That's why I asked to see you.

220
00:14:17,030 --> 00:14:19,500
Don't just drift aimlessly.
Think about what to do next,

221
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:22,070
and if there's anything
you're passionate about.

222
00:14:22,770 --> 00:14:24,030
I'll support you
in whatever you choose.

223
00:14:29,770 --> 00:14:33,880
I'm finding a center for Gi Man
where he can get physical therapy.

224
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:37,550
I think it's better he lives there.

225
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:39,150
Of course,

226
00:14:39,150 --> 00:14:40,750
only if you agree, Na Ra.

227
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:42,420
And...

228
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:47,190
once you can stand on your own feet
as a productive member of society,

229
00:14:47,590 --> 00:14:49,430
I'll turn over the full amount
to you.

230
00:14:51,230 --> 00:14:53,400
Do you understand what I'm saying?

231
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:57,130
You mean my brother...

232
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:02,570
did this for us?
Because he was worried about us?

233
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,210
That's right.

234
00:15:08,210 --> 00:15:10,580
Oh, Gi Chan...

235
00:15:58,560 --> 00:15:59,930
Na Ra.

236
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:03,000
Go make us some noodles.

237
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:05,800
Hwang Na Ra.

238
00:16:09,770 --> 00:16:12,640
Honestly, this girl.
The sun's high in the sky,

239
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:15,480
and she won't even get up? Na Ra!

240
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:17,280
Hwang Na Ra!

241
00:16:18,620 --> 00:16:19,620
Good grief.

242
00:16:24,090 --> 00:16:26,590
Mom, don't look for me. Take care.

243
00:16:27,090 --> 00:16:28,130
Na Ra.

244
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:43,570
Goodness. Oh, no.

245
00:16:44,540 --> 00:16:47,210
I can't believe I raised
such ungrateful kids.

246
00:16:51,980 --> 00:16:56,490
Mom, I'm hungry.
Give me something to eat.

247
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:00,860
I'm stuck with this dimwit.

248
00:17:01,860 --> 00:17:03,830
How am I supposed to survive
on my own?

249
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,630
Oh, dear...

250
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,600
Oh, dear.

251
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:21,180
Right. The house.

